# Quartz Publishing Rules

## Context

The vault publishes to Quartz at docs.noclocks.dev/noclocksvault using a three-branch workflow.

## Branch Workflow

| Branch | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `develop` | Raw Obsidian content with wikilinks |
| `main` | GitHub-viewable content (converted links) |
| `gh-pages` | Deployed Quartz static site |

## Quartz Configuration

Configuration in `quartz/quartz.config.ts`:
- Base URL: `docs.noclocks.dev/noclocksvault`
- Ignored: `05-SYSTEM/Templates`, `99-ARCHIVES`, `.obsidian`, `private`

## Publishing Considerations

When creating publishable content:
- Set `publish: true` in frontmatter
- Avoid Obsidian-only plugin syntax in published notes
- Ensure linked notes exist or are also published
- Use standard markdown features for compatibility

## Theme Configuration

Light mode colors:
- Primary: `#1a365d` (deep blue)
- Secondary: `#2c5282`

Dark mode colors:
- Primary: `#63b3ed` (light blue)
- Secondary: `#4299e1`

Fonts:
- Header: Schibsted Grotesk
- Body: Source Sans Pro
- Code: IBM Plex Mono

## Static Assets

- Place images in `04-RESOURCES/Assets/Images/`
- Use relative paths for embeds
- Banners in `04-RESOURCES/Assets/Banners/`
- Logos in `04-RESOURCES/Assets/Logos/`
